Mutual hospitality between all monasteries seems to have been regarded as a matter of ,course ; and Bede sees in this one fulfilment of Christ's promise, that those who forsake earthly possessions and relations for His sake, shall receive an hundredfold even in this present world 3. The guest-house or hospice was a separate building, and the head of this department, the ‘ Praepositus Hospitum,’ was an important officer of the community 4.

The discipline of the monastery was in the hands of the abbot, assisted by the prior, or, as he was then called,
